    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName><hi rend="italic">From Mr. Darwin, Down, Beckenham.</hi></placeName>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>When you answer my queries be so good as to state how much land has been used in cultivating the varieties.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> like to at least allude to this point. How many seedlings have you raised in any one year?</p>
                        <p> C. D.</p>
                        <p rend="left">March 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 <hi rend="italic">Mr</hi>.] <hi rend="italic">altered from</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Mrs.</hi>’</note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.2 How … year? 1.3] <hi rend="italic">added</hi></note>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12530.xml">letter to James Torbitt, 10 March 1880</ref>.</note>
                <note xml:id="foot.f2">See letters to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4777.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">James Torbitt</ref>, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12521.xml">6 March [1880]</ref> and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12530.xml">10 March 1880</ref>.</note>
            </div>
        
